CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 29, 1961, pg. 24, reads: "Steeler Power for 1961 NFL Title Chase - Happy Lad - Fred Williamson, defensive frosh back of 1960, is being touted to succeed departed Johnny Orr, as pass catcher. The ex-Northwestern ace is happy, he says, "because offensive end is my dish."  he is 6'2" and weights 218."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Steelers football player no. 46 Fred Williamson, jumping to catch ball, on athletic field at Slippery Rock State Teachers College
